    1) IntroductionÂ§

    This page contains information related to the final exam logistics and practice exam materials.

    2) LogisticsÂ§

    • The final exam will be held on Monday, 19 May from 1:30-4:30pm on Johnson Track (Z-center, third floor).

    • The exam is likely to emphasize material covered after the midterm, but it is a cumulative exam, so material from before the midterm can also be tested.

    • The exam will be given on paper, so please make sure to bring one or more pencils with you.

    • The exam is closed-book, and you may not use electronics of any kind during the exam (including computers, calculators, phones, tablets, music players, etc.).

    • Proctors will be available to answer administrative questions and clarify specifications of problems, but they should not be relied on for help with solving the problems.

    • If you require accommodations for the exam (with a note from DAS), please e-mail 6.101-personal@mit.edu with the subject line "6.101 Final Exam Accommodations." Please contact us by Tuesday, 13 May if you require accommodations.

    3) Practice MaterialsÂ§

    Practice materials for the exam are now available in the form of exams from previous semesters. The Spring 2023 exam was a two-hour exam that did not cover the material from exam 1, and Fall 2024 was given in a different format. The exams from Fall 2023 and Spring 2024 are likely to be closer in terms of length and coverage than the other exams.

    In order to best make use of these practice exams, we strongly suggest working through them in as authentic an environment as possible (i.e., on paper, with the time limit noted on the exam and without access to external resources).

    • Fall 2024 Final Exam
    • Spring 2024 Final Exam
    • Fall 2023 Final Exam
    • Spring 2023 Exam 2

    If you have any questions as you're working through these, please let us know!

    3.1) Answers to Practice ExamsÂ§

    Answers to the practice exams are available below, but you are strongly encouraged not to look at them until after you have tried the exams yourself (ideally under normal exam conditions). Note that many of the questions have multiple correct answers and that the answers documents only show one such answer.

    These documents also intentionally only include answers, without detailed explanations, so that you can try to work through the problems again if you arrived at a wrong answer. They also generally only contain one possible answer, even where multiple correct answers exist. If you are unsure about why an answer is right (or if you think an answer might be wrong, or if you have an alternative answer that you are unsure of), feel free to ask about it in open lab hours, instructors office hours, or via the e-mail lists!

    • Answers to Fall 2024 Final Exam
    • Answers to Spring 2024 Final Exam
    • Answers to Fall 2023 Final Exam
    • Answers to Spring 2023 Exam 2

    4) Additional Study ResourcesÂ§

    It may be useful to review the exam study tips and practice exams from exam 1 as you prepare for the final. In addition to reviewing the readings and recitation material (and potentially doing the extra problems recommended therein) there are extra coding practice problems related to the labs available on the readings page under "Extra Practice."

    There are also additional Environment Diagrams: Classes example problems.

    You may ask TAs in open lab hours or email 6.101-help if you have any questions.
